inn1.comm: short and side, Strauss chased it, went for the cut but ended mistiming it to point
pitched up this time, just on a good length outside off, appeared to hold its line, watches it through to the keeper
comes back in from a good length outside off, fends it away into the leg side
short and wide, goes for it and it pays off, cut away hard through point for a boundary
bowled full outside off, driven wide of mid-off and extra cover for a single
bowled on a good length on middle, gets on the back foot and pushes it down towards midwicket
bowls it on a good length on middle, turns it into the leg side towards midwicket
beaten! Took off after landing, short on middle and beat the outside edge as it moved away with some extra bounce as Strauss tried to withdraw, excellent carry to the keeper
that's gone all the way! Banged it in short, Strauss was late on the pull but it proved effective, got the top edge and cleared third man comfortably, six!
pitched it full this time, driven wide of Johnson at mid-off for three runs, good intent from Strauss here
back of a length outside off, bowled at 141.7 kmph, angles it wide of Hussey at point and scampers through for a single

brilliant catch by Hopes! Strauss had timed it well, it was bowled full on leg stump, he clipped it elegantly but uppishly, Hopes threw himself to his left at square leg and plucked it inches from the ground
short of a good length on leg stump, pushed into the leg side towards midwicket
back of a length on middle, turned away into the leg side wide of square leg for a single
short of a good length outside off, moved away a hint, he played at it, got a thick outside edge but it landed short of second slip

gone! Short on leg stump, Shah walks across to tickle it fine, gets a faint touch and it goes through to Paine, two down are England and they've been hit early, Paine took a good catch diving well to his left
back of a length on the off, taps it back down onto the pitch
back of a length on the off, tries to turn it to midwicket, gets an inside edge onto his thighs
back of a length on the off, defended into the off side
good shot, bowled short and wide and he ensures he doesn't waste the opportunity, cutting it hard into the ground wide of the point fielder for a boundary
bowled full on the off and it's moving in, pushed into the leg side
bowled on a good length outside off, holds its line but he gets some good bounce, left alone to the keeper
pushed into the of side off the back foot
bowled short outside off, Collingwood senses a chance and pulls it through midwicket for two runs
poor length, short and wide, bisects the gap between cover and point, just smacks it off the back foot and earns a boundary
short of a good length on the off, pushed back to the bowler
oversteps, freehit coming, back of a length outside off, guided down to third man for a single
bowled full outside off, moves away and rams it down the ground through mid-on for a boundary
bowled on a good length on the off, moves forward, covers it well and defends it solidly to cover
fullish, he's rock solid in defense as he plays it away into the off side
back of a length on the off, moves back, stands tall and taps it to cover
angling in towards the off stump, gets across and defends it wide of the bowler
short of a good length on the off, tapped into the leg side in front of short fine for a single
short of a length on the off, moves back and dabs it short of cover
bowled full on the off, pushed through straight to extra cover
short of a good length on middle and off, defended in front of the bowler into the off side
bowled on a good length on middle, shuffles across and works it to midwicket
tight line outside off, gets towards it and presses it towards cover
sharp fielding by Ponting, gets forward and defends it to extra cover and and the Australian captain records a direct hit at the striker's end but Collingwood isn't risking a single, not to Ponting
bowled at 148 kmph just marginally outside off, gets across and pushes it back to the bowler
full outside off, pushed firmly just wide of Ponting, maybe he got a finger to it, went wide of mid-off for a single
angling it in towards off, drives it gently to a slightly deepish mid-off for a single
bowled shortish on the off, pulled down straight to midwicket
bowled it short of a good length on the off, rocks back and defends it to cover
attempting to get it in the blockhole, digs it out back to the bowler
unless you have more of these deliveries, the extra bounce again, took the batsman by surprise, shot off from a good length on the off and he took  his bottom hand off to keep it down
beautifully timed, pitched up outside off, gets forward and eases it through that gap between cover and mid-off
back of a length on the off, rocks back and punches it down to mid-off
bowled at 123kmph, lands on a good length on the off, jabs it down to mid-off
Collingwood's looking good, carrying forward his good form, full on the off stump, length delivery and he has a swing of the arms, crashing it over the bowler's head for a boundary
more conventional this time, an offdrive, overpitched and he gives it the treatment, smacking it through the covers for four more
short of a good length on the off, watchful this time as he nudges it wide of the bowler
back of a length outside off, cracked off the back foot straight to Ponting at short cover

clears the ropes! Not quite bowled on a length there but he had made his mind up, got forward and just struck it through the line, launched it high and handsome over the ropes at long-on, well timed again
...and starts with a wide, down the leg side, concedes a free run
short of a good length on the off, pushed to short cover

run out chance missed, poor judgment by Denly, pushed to the right of Johnson, he just had to move a few steps, collect and take aim, he had plenty of time to do so but missed, and conceded overthrows the process, five runs in all, the single was never on
tremendous pull, back of a length on middle, moved across and dismissed it hard through square leg for a boundary
short and wide, bread and butter for Collingwood who cuts it disdainfully through point and cover, Johnson taking time to settle in here
he's making it look really easy here, short on middle, moves across,. swivels and pulls it down to fine leg for a single
pushed wide of mid-off on the front foot for a single
gets forward and taps it in front of cover for another easily taken single
short of a good length on the off, jabs it towards point
gave him the charge there, bowled it on a good length, pushed it respectfully towards mid-off
getting it to leave the right hander just a hint, guided down to third man for a single
beaten! Tempting line outside off, swings away as he is sucked into the drive, just escapes the outside edge
angles it away from the right hander, short on the off, Collingwood taps it towards point

got him, well taken by Paine! Collingwood was tempted to pull that , short on middle, shuffled and tried to pull it through square leg, the extra bounce did the trick there for Johnson and so did the pace, a thin touch to the glove and Paine snapped it one-handed timing his leap to perfection
bowled fullish on the off, defended confidently down to cover
back of a length on the off, moves across and taps it to cover
fishing for it outside off, holds its line and he makes no contact
short outside off, bowled at 142 kmph, leaves it be
fine leg is a little too square,straying on the pads, Denly got a faint tickle to it and raced down to the fence
bowled at 138.8kmph, square drive through point and cover for a single into the deep
getting it to shape away a hint from the left hander, defended towards point with a slightly open face
short of a good length outside off, gets a stride forward and runs it down to third man for a single
tries to push it through cover but ends up getting a thick edge down to third man
beaten! Probing him outside off, Morgan prods at it, it comes back in a touch and deceives him with the extra bouncer, just escaped the outside edge
bowled at 139.3 kmph, short on middle, punched back to the bowler
slowed it down, bowled it at 124.2 kmph, pushed off the back foot to cover
bowled full on the off, driven down sweetly but straight to mid-off
slower one bowled short outside off, at 125.3 kmph, cut down to point
a snorter that, bowled at 141 but appeared to come on to him a lot quicker than that, reacted a little late to that bouncer but all ok in the end
short outside off, the legcutter to the right hander, runs it down to third man to keep the strike
straying on the pads, and yet again, just a faint tickle earns him a boundary, too square is the fine-leg fielder
bowled on a good length on the off, taps it down to deep cover for a single
trying to get it to leave the left hander, shuffles a hint and knocks it down
short and wide, tries to chop it past point but it's too quick for him, makes no contact
Ponting misfields at short cover, driven to him on the bounce and he ends up palming it off to long-on
nipping back in a hint, works it away wristily down to deep square leg for a single
fullish on the off, pushed through the line to extra cover
short of a good length on middle, tucked down towards that squarish fine leg for a single
cut uppishly but just short of Hussey at point, short and wide and he struggled to keep it down
slower one bowled full outside off, pushed down to cover
back of a length outside off, chopped down through cover for a single
lands on a good length outside off, walks across and threads that into the deep on the off side for a single
back of a length outside off, chopped down towards cover
slower one bowled full, at 117 kmph, pushed to short cover
bowled quick, and on a good length outside off, Morgan was caught walking down to that one, tried to push it past cover, failed to get his bat to it and was beaten
bowled at 138kmph, in that channel outside off, fishes for it and gets beaten again
nips back in just a hint, drops it down in front of point
lands full outside off, moves across and defends it to cover
bangs it short on middle, is struck on the ribs as he tries to work it away through midwicket

got him! Short of a length outside off and gets it to move away, Denly chases it, trying to get it past point but gets a thick edge and Paine again does a good job stretching full length to his right and taking a smart catch
nice start, bowled full outside off, flicked away through square leg for three runs
nips back in from a good length outside off, turns his bat to work it away but ends up getting a thick inside edge behind square
fullish outside of, dabs that wide of cover for a single
back of a length outside off, cuts it down to point for  a single

dropped by Hopes, a sitter, Morgan was clearly frustrated, bowled full outside off, tried to clear extra cover but he ended up slicing it towards deep point, plenty of time for Hopes to position himself, looked good to watch it through into his palms but spilled it in the end. Has turned 180  after that brilliant catch to dismiss Strauss
cut away through point for a single
full and wide, pushed through to mid-off
back of a length outside off, goes for a cut, gets a thick edge down to third man for a single to bring up the 100

Davies sent back early on his debut, nipped back in this time, short of a good length outside off, tried to defend it off the back foot, it moved in off the pitch just a hint, took the inside edge and knocked back the off stump
shortish outside off, holds its line this time, left alone to the keeper
bowled full outside off, driven down to deep cover for a single
angling it in the pads, tries to drive it through midwicket, gets an inside edge onto his pads
bowled full on the off, driven through to mid-on
bowled full on middle, pushed back to the bowler on the bounce, driven hard but straight to the bowler
sharp and quick bouncer at 145.2 kmph, Wright ducks under it comfortably
pushed down gently towards mid-on
lands on a good length on the off, defended down towards cover

Morgan's gone! Short outside off, just a fraction outside the off stump, goes for the cut, gets a thin edge straight to the keeper, perhaps too close to play that shot but he was struggling to get the runs
bowled fullish on the off, presents the full face and plays it back to the bowler
short of a good length on the off, dropped off the back foot to cover
attacking shot, bowled short outside off rocked back and pulled it hard over midwicket for a pressure-relieving boundary
banged in short on middle, worked away to square leg for a single
short of a good length outside off, punched wide of cover and scampers through for a quick single
short and wide, cut down to third man for a single
lovely shot, full and wide, in the lot and he drove it handsomely through the line wide of the bowler and mid-off for a boundary
shortish outside off, tries to punch it away from his body, gets a thick inside edge wide of square leg for a single
lands on a good length outside off, driven firmly but straight to cover
came back in just a hint, pushed off the back foot towards short cover
came back in  again and Bresnan's really lucky this time, just pushing at it off the crease, gets an inside edge down to the fine-leg boundary
back of a length on the off, pushed into the off side
the slower legcutter bowled at 114.5 kmph, tapped towards midwicket, Wright was interested in the single but Bresnan sent him back at the right time
a hint of seam movement away from the batsman, in the channel outside off, left alone
short of a good length on the off, knocked down to short cover
short outside off, turns back in, smacked down to deep cover
tossed it up just a fraction outside off, defended into the leg side
pushed it fuller outside off, held its line, left alone
threw it up on middle, worked away through to deep square leg
shuffles well across, Hauritz slows it down, worked away to short fine
flatter, turning in just a hint, pushed to short cover
swinging away there, bowled at 136.9 kmph, pitched it on a good length outside off, left alone
short outside off, chops it down to third man for a single
full and wide, drives at it hard, there's a widish slip in place but the thick outside edge is well past him, four more to the score
back of a length on the off, pushed down to cover from the crease
full and wide again and Wright chases it, driving it hard towards sweeper cover for a single
full on the off stump, pitched up, pushed down to mid-off for a single
gets on his knee and sweeps to deep square leg
tossed up on middle and leg and driven down the ground to long-on
slower through the air, gets forward and knocks it to the on side
shuffles and trickles it down to square leg
slow through the air again and defended with soft hands
commits early to the sweep and places it cleanly to deep square leg
slower ball outside off and tapped to the off side
short of a length and clipped down to deep square leg
fired it on a full length on the off stump, he pushes it firmly back to Johnson who nearly back flicks it onto the stumps at the other end
dishes it out full and wide and he drives down to deep extra cover
just dropped short! Bresnan wasn't in full control of the pull but he hits it quite flat and Hopes at deep square runs forward and takes it on the bounce
gets forward and pushes it very firmly just wide of mid-off
tosses it outside off and he opts to defend
goes for a forceful drive off a full delivery and he finds sweeper cover
full outside off and driven to extra cover
tossed up outside off and defended on the front foot
goes right across his stumps and clips it to deep square leg
gets on his knee very early, exposes all three stumps and sweeps to short fine leg
pushes it to sweeper cover for a single
lunges well forward to drive and the ball balloons off the top edge and rolls to third man
turns his wrists and clips him just wide of mid-on and has to scamper for that single, throw misses the stumps
comes round the wicket and Wright pushes it to mid-off
bends his knee and attempts a flashy square drive but he mistimes it and finds point
tries to slice it square of the wicket on the off side but he finds Hussey again at point
on target straightaway on the off stump, Bresnan gets a half stride forward and defends
fired in on a good length outside off and he's driven down to deep cover
gets a bit of late swing inwards and the batsman ends up punching it straight back to the bowler
hits the deck hard and Aleem Dar penalises him for that bouncer, that was quick
hops at the crease and steers it just wide of point and takes off but his partner sends him back
stays beside the line and plays a punched drive to Ferguson at square third man
nips back in off the seam and the batsman stays at the crease and nearly edges it onto the stumps
slow through the air, he waits for it to turn before cutting to deep point
comes forward early and defends to the off side
stays at the crease and times the punch very well to beat Hauritz who dives to his right
quicker through the air, taps it to the off side and tells his partner to wait
tries to swipe him across the line on bended knee and misses it completely
stays back and cuts to point
cramps Wright for room but h responds with a solid defensive shot
bangs in in short of a length and swings it in, he shuffles and clips it to fine leg
stays at the crease and clips him with the movement to deep square leg
bends down and gets out of the way of a quick bouncer, Aleem Dar doesn't signal anything
aims for the yorker and Wright edges the ball onto his boot
fires it in on middle and leg and he mistimes the drive to cover
full outside off an driven to sweeper cover
full outside off and driven to the off side and thats the 50 stand
slow through the air and defended with a dead bat
makes room, waits for the turn and cuts to the off side
quicker through the air and whipped to midwicket
full outside off and squired towards cover
stays back and clips him to the on side
he hammers this to Hussey at point who fumbles a bit
clips him to deep square leg and thinks of the second run
shuffles and clips him down to fine leg
been a while since the ball was lofted, he clears midwicket and the ball lands in the middle of nowhere
stays back and punches him to the off side
full outside off and driven to cover
clean hit, tossed up on the off stump, he gets on his knee and slog sweeps him high and far over deep midwicket
makes room and cuts him to the off side
pushed to the off side
into the second tier! Can we have the ball back please, gentlemen? Tossed up outside off and Wright plays the shot in his mind before getting on his knee and slog sweeping him over deep square leg
kicks up a bit and he taps it to point
kicks up outside off and he punches him down to  third man
gets a half stride forward and defends back to the bowler
gets forward and pushes it to the off side for a single
gets a half stride forward and chops it down to point
stays beside the line and taps it to point
the slower ball and he bangs it in short, ducks under the bouncer and wide called
gets beside the line and chops it down to backward point
gets a generous full toss outside off which he fails to put away because Ponting does really well to get a hand to it at short cover
shuffles and clips him down to midwicket
just a tad risky but Bresnan won't mind, he gets forward and chips it in the air dangerously towards Ponting's right at short cover, he dives in vain and the ball beats the fielder giving the chase
clipped to the on side for a single
down the leg side and he gets a faint tickle and fine leg runs across and mops up
looking more and more dangerous, pitched up outside off and the batsman gets forward and scoops it well over mid-off's reach
gets across and chops it down to the off side
mistimes the cut and the ball rolls to the off side
grants him width outside off and he places it towards deep point
full outside off and driven on the front foot to sweeper cover
very smartly played indeed, Johnson hits the deck hard and takes the pace off the ball, Bresnan gets beside the line and effortlessly punches it wide of backward and bisects two fielders in the deep
goes for a wild swish off a short ball and misses it completely
lands it on a good length outside off and he decides not to offer a shot
Australia losing the plot  a bit here, Johnson digs it in short down the leg side and he gets a faint trickle down to fine leg
taps it to the off side and Bresnan brings up his fifty! Very valuable indeed
Terrible delivery, short down the leg side and Bresnan swivels and pulls him easily to fine leg, the fielder was too square
full on middle and leg and clipped to deep square leg
punches him hard but finds short cover
hits the deck really hard and he gets under that bouncer
mid-on is pushed back and Wright takes the aerial route and scoops it towards that fielder
chips it in the air again down to mid-on

Paine pouches his fifth victim, soft dismissal in the end, he chases a full and wide delivery and gets a thick outside edge to Paine, Wright should be happy with his efforts for getting England this far
hits a good length on the off stump and he stays back and defends
shuffles and clips him down to midwicket
stays at the crease and punches it to mid-off
goes for a booming cover drive and chops it onto his boot off the inside edge
he's lucky to still be there, he chases a full and wide delivery and ends up scooping it towards third man, the ball just drops short of the fielder
cheeky and innovative indeed, Johnson bangs it in short, Bresnan sways backwards and plays a cheeky upper cut directly over first slip, the fine leg fielder dives in vain
gets forward and pushes it to cover
this one skids off the surface and nearly takes the outside edge
full marks for timing, hits a fullish length outside off, he gets a half stride forward and times the punch really well down to deep point, third man scampers across in vain
tapped just wide of cover and sets off quickly
gets forward and punches it to mid-off
angles it on middle and leg and he clips it down to mid-on
hits a good length outside off and he steers it wide of backward point
don't ask me how that missed the nick and the top of the off stump, kicks up off a good length and Swann plays all around it
he gets forward, checks his drive and ends up spooning it right between mid-off and cover
Paine makes a valiant attempt at a sixth catch! The batsman chases a wide delivery and the thick outside edge just beats Paine's dive to his right
action replay and still no slip! This is angled a lot further across the right-hander and Bresnan chases it, Paine dives to his right and well only first slip would have taken that
gets a half stride forward and defends
reaches out and gets an outside edge to third man
bangs it in short and he miscues the pull a bit but fortunately for Bresnan the ball drops short of deep square leg
gets forward and taps it to the off side
tries to slice it through the off side but the ball ends up slicing him in half, good inward movement
effortless! Siddle pitches it up outside off and Swann gets forward and times the checked drive very well and beats Ponting at short cover
aims for the yorker and he squirts out the low full toss to mid-on
fired in full outside off and jams it out to mid-off
firm punch but straight to Hussey at point
stays beside the line and Hussey is kept busy again at point
the frustration gets to Bresnan who makes room to crash that past point but he's beaten for pace
shuffles across his stumps and whips it down to wide long-on and pushes hard for the second run
drags the length back a bit and once again Bresnan tries to wham it past the off side but he ends up swishing at thin air

excellent work by the Australians, Swann reaches out and angles the ball down to third man, Swann wants the second, he's always struggling but fails to time his dive, the throw from Hauritz is flat and quick and Paine whips off the bails, Bowden doesn't need the replay
stays back and taps it down to the off side
digs it short down the leg side and close to being called a wide
stays beside the line and chops it down to deep point
gets right across his stumps and mows a low full toss straight to mid-on
fires it on the blockhole and he makes room to wwhack it anywhere but the ball takes the edge and rolls to the on side
that brings the 250, Bresnan backs away and whacks a back of a length delivery over mid-on, clears the fielder comfortably, more of a flat-batted swat
timber! Bresnan backs away to crash that over the on side but Lee fires in a yorker and flattens the middle stump, that ends Bresnan's resistance, will it be a match-winning knock? Let's wait and see
Onions is all at sea as Lee fires it on a good length outside off and nearly takes the edge
he nervously makes room and squirts it towards cover to get off the strike
the ball skids through and hurries Anderson as he looks to clip it to the on side, England in a tricky situation here in the Powerplay
that's more like it, drags the length back and Anderson shuffles and easily clips it away to the on side
makes a bit of room and forces it to mid-on
tries to lash that square of the wicket through the off side but he misses it completely
drags the length back and the batsman gets under that bouncer, close to being penalised
well he hoicks him over midwicket this time but the timing isn't good enough to fetch a boundary

confusion galore! Seemed like a sports blooper, Anderson goes right back and across and nearly trods onto his stumps as he works it to midwicket, first run comfortably taken but there's confusion about the second, Anderson wants it, Onions doesn't, Onions has no option but to leave his crease but he turns back and it's too late as Paine collects the throw from Ferguson whips off the bails

inn2.comm: bowled on a good length outside off, moving away a hint, gets to it, opens the face and guides it to point
lands on a good length outside off, testing line, leaving the right hander, left alone
bowled full on the off, seaming away, driven with a full face to mid-off
angling away from the right hander, guided down to third man for a single
back of a length outside off, left alone to the keeper, moving away a hint
short of a good length on the off, rocks back and drops it short of cover
short of a good length on middle, turned away through square leg for a single
back of a length outside off, he gets into position early, rocking back and smashing it through midwicket for a boundary
got him! Sweet revenge for Onions, who lands this on a tempting length just outside off, sucks Paine into the drive who plays loosely at it, gets a thin edge straight through to Davies
lands on a good length outside off, Ponting gets a stride forward and gets an inside edge onto his pads as he tries to defend
angling it in on middle, Ponting gets across and drives it down to midwicket
similar delivery to the one that got rid of Paine, full, driving length but no movement here, Ponting decides to leave it be
Watson goes after it, he's been out pulling once in this competition but he connects it well this time, short and wide and he dispatches it over mid-on
short of a good length outside off, moving away, left alone
short of a good length on middle, at 141 kmph, defended off the back foot into the off side
straying down the leg side there, called a wide
bowled full on middle, worked away through to deep square leg
lands on a good length on the off, gets forward, closes the face and taps it into the leg side

got the leading edge, the late swing there and he almost made a mess of his attempt to drive that fullish delivery through midwicket, checked his shot at the last moment and it rolled down to extra cover
bowled on a good length outside off, pushed through to cover
short and wide, cut down to third man for a single
back of a length outside off, angling in just a hint, left alone
back of a length outside off, punched back to the bowler
lands on a good length outside off, gets forward and pushes it down the pitch
drove it uppishly but was struck really hard, overpitched outside off and Ponting couldn't stop himself from going after it, crashed it past a diving extra cover for a boundary
bowled fullish on middle, driven straight to midwicket
in the channel outside off, appeared to hold its line, slightly short, left alone to the keeper
bowled full on the off, pushed hard through the line to mid-off
short of a good length on the off, gets a thick inside edge down to square leg, kept just a little low there as it nipped back in
a bit of extra bounce there, Ponting had come forward to defend but took his bottom-hand off and played it down onto the pitch

atrocious fielding, Morgan the culprit, bowled full outside off, pushed to short cover where Morgan needlessly hurls it at the keeper thinking he's 10 feet tall and meets the fine-leg boundary, well done
full on the off stump, driven through the line to the bowler
lands on a good length on the off, pushed down to mid-on off the front foot
bowled on a length outside off at 139 kmph, pushed through to cover
bowled full on the off, driven hard into the ground back to the bowler

misfield, Bresnan the man to blame this time, full on the off, driven with a full face past the outstretched hands of the bowler and Bresnan dived over it and didn't get any part of his body onto it for all that effort
beaten there, got some bounce and movement away from the right hander to beat the outside edge as he tried to run it down
sweetly timed, short outside off, gets on the back foot and just punches it square, well wide of point, all the way to the ropes, raced away
terrible delivery, full on the pads, clipped away wide of short fine for four more
straighter on middle, gets across to push it down the ground towards mid-on
bowled on a good length on middle and leg, turned away to midwicket
Ponting's in good touch and it shows from that flowing drive through cover, pitched up, it was there to hit but he picked the gap perfectly, placing it through cover and mid-off
hurling it full on middle, driven down to mid-off
slower one bowled short on the off stump, turned into the leg side wide of midwicket for a single
bowled full on middle, driven off the front foot down to mid-on
bowled full on middle, Ponting gets front and across and drives it down to mid-on
lands on a good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
driven hard past the bowler, pitched up on middle and off by Onions and he presents the full face, that demanded more effort from Onions on his follow-through there, didn't try hard to stop that
banged in short on middle, ducks under it comfortably, it's too high and Aleem Dar's called it a wide
another one, gifting away runs here, short ball banged in down the leg side
slower one bowled short on leg stump, wrong line again, moves across and whips it fine, wide of the fielder in the deep, for a couple of runs
the half-centurion starts poorly, dragged it short on middle, Ponting's not going to forgive those, rocks back and pulls it wide of short fine
short of a good length outside off, comes back in, defended to cover
another freebie, short and wide, Ponting gets into position and cuts it through point and cover for another four
short on middle, tucked away through midwicket for a single
played it nicely, some extra bounce for Bresnan, Watson got on top of it and dabbed it down to third man
bowled full on the off stump, pushed through to extra cover
short ball again, Watson fails to make use of it,  mistimes a pull to midwicket
bouncer this time, Watson went for the hook but that came on to him quickly and he missed, trying for a Collingwood-like dismissal there
banged in short outside off, at 136.2 kmph, struck hard on the shoulders as he went for the pull, deflected wide of point for a single
that short one took Ponting by surprise there, had shaped up for his favourite pull but it bounced more than he expected, checked his shot and played it down wide of fine leg for a couple of runs
short of a good length outside off, appears to hold its line, left alone to the keeper
well timed, the offcutter bowled sightly short outside off, waited for it to nip in and just the opened the face to guide it wide of Collingwood at point for a couple more
shortish on the off, pulled down wide of midwicket for a single

appeal for caught-behind, short on the off, the bounce takes Ponting by surprise, goes for the pull, misses and it clips the shoulder on the way to the keeper, England went up but Bowden rightly turned them down
bowled on a good length outside off, pushed wide of cover point for a single
back of a length outside off, run down to third man
shortish on the off stump, gets forward and blocks it hard back to the bowler
short of a good length outside off, tapped down to point from the crease
another bouncer, trying to ruffle them up with short ones here, Watson ducks under it easily
back of a length on the off, worked away towards midwicket
banged in short, too may of them here, Watson latches onto it and pulls it wide of short fine and deep square leg for a boundary
bouncer again, too high in this case, Watson thought of the pull but he couldn't reach it
fuller, just on a good length outside off, defended solidly to cover
slightly short on the off and nipping in, the offcutter, defended straight back to the bowler
short of a length outside off, cut down towards point who takes it on the bounce
appeal for lbw, angling in towards the right hander, nips back in from a good length and strikes him on the thighs as he comes forward, too high
shortish on middle and leg, turned away wide of midwicket for a single
back of a length on the off, gets a thick inside edge as he tries to defend on the off side, steals a single
back of a length on the off, punched down to deep point for one more
hitting the pitch hard, bowled at 137.1 kmph, defended down to short cover
fullish on the off stump, gets front and across and defends it back to the bowler
short on the off, punched through to deep cover for a single
bowled on middle and off, drives wide of the bowler to mid-on
fullish on the off, driven down to long-on for a single
back of a length on middle, taps it back to the bowler
slower one there, the offcutter, gets a big stride forward and defends it back to the bowler
back of a length on the off, chops it down to point off the back foot
shortish on the off, drops it short of point and steals a quick single
nipping in towards off stump, defends it rock solid back to the bowler
short of a good length on middle, defended down to midwicket
a bit of hesitation out there in the middle, punched to cover, Ponting was interested in a single and ran halfway down the pitch but Watson sent him back in time
shortish on middle, pulled down wide of Denly at deep midwicket for a single
back of a length on the off, pushed back to the bowler
straying on the pads, clipped away to fine leg for a single
fullish on the off, just pushes it wide of the bowler and midwicket for a single
short of a good length on middle and leg, whipped away down to deep midwicket for a single
driving length, just outside off, pushed through to short cover
back of a length on middle, pushes it back onto the pitch
bouncer, called a wide, too high and Davies did a good job snapping it
short of a good length outside off, run down to third man for a single
angling in towards middle and off, pushed into the gap between the bowler and midwicket for a single
back of a length on middle, worked away to midwicket
slower one this time, bowled at 119.1 kmph, turned away wide of midwicket for a single
shortish on middle, whipped away into the deep on the leg side for one more
came back in, it was the offcutter, tried to run it down to third man, was struck high on the pads, they steal a single behind point
nicely played by Watson, short outside off, run down to third man for a single
bowled full outside off, driven straight to mid-off
lands on a good length on middle, gets across and turns it to midwicket
shortish on the off, eased through to deep cover for a single
angling it in on the pads, pushed through to deep midwicket for one more
short on the off, cut down towards point off the back foot
short outside off and turns back in, defended back to the bowler
pushed it full outside off, defended with a lunge to extra cover
short on the off, pulled away really hard but straight to Denly at deep midwicket
short on middle, moves back and presses it away to deep square leg
just a hint outside off, whipped away to deep midwicket for a single
tosses it up outside off, driven down to long-on for a single
shortish on the off, guided down to point off the front foot
shortish on middle, pulled down wide of fine leg for a single
short of a good length on the off, pushed back to the bowler
full on middle, driven through the line towards long-on for a single
short of a good length outside off, punched wide of mid-off for a quick single
turning in from a good length outside off, taps it wide of point for a single
quicker through the air, bowled full outside off, driven down to long-on, brings up the 100
full outside off, gets across and works it down to midwicket
third half-century of the competition for Ponting, driven down the ground to long-on

didn't get hold of it, not as much as he wanted to, tossed up on middle and he slog-swept it over long-on, the fielder had to run a few paces back towards the ropes, Luke Wright, and he got his hands to it as he tried to cup that over his head but ended up palming it over the ropes
pushed down to long-on for a single
worked away off the back foot into the leg side for a single
lands on a good length outside off, pushed down towards cover
pushed off the front foot through cover for a single
angling it towards middle, driven through to long-on for a single
tossed up outside off, covers it well, closes the face and turns it to midwicket
Watson reaches his half-century with that drive to long-off, had a poor start to the series and he'll be relieved to reach that landmark
short outside off, cut down towards deep point for a single
bowled quicker at 96.9 kmph, pushed back to the bowler
turned away off the front foot wide of midwicket for one more
straight on middle, tickles it in front of long leg for a single to keep the strike
bowled on a good length on middle, defended back to the bowler
bowled on a good length on middle, glanced down to fine leg for a single
fullish on the off stump, driven uppishly just wide of Ponting for a single
slower one bowled short outside off, guided down to third man for a single
back of a length on middle, pushed off the back foot to midwicket
nipped back in from a good length outside off, is struck high on the pads as he tries to jab it down to third man
angling in towards middle, comes across and works it down to midwicket
shot! Bowled full outside off, driven wide of an extra cover into the deep for a couple more
short of a good length on the off, gets back and defends it onto the pitch
short of a good length outside off, plugged down through the off side to deep point
back of a length on the off, pushed back to the bowler
hurling it on middle and leg, defended to midwicket
sides down the leg side and he easily tickles it away
gets a little adventurous by chipping it in the air but the ball dips and lands in front of long-on
gets beside the line and steers it to deep point
opens the blade and angles it down to third man
Ponting knew where the fielder was, friendly half volley, the slower delivery and Ponting lofts through the line and clears mid-off
gets  behind the line and defends
fullish in length and firmly driven past the bowler and down to mid-off
bowls a half volley on the pads and he easily works it behind square on the on side
how close was that to the outside edge? Lovely delivery, just holds its line and beats Ponting who gets forward and shapes to play the off drive
gets bat on ball this time and pushes him to cover
aims for the yorker length and Ponting gets across and pushes a low full toss through the line to long-on
makes use of the width outside off to glide it down to third man
gets right across his stumps and tucks it with the turn to short fine leg
goes across and pushes it down to midwicket
fullish on middle and leg, pushed down the ground to long-on
quicker through the air and tucked to square leg
comes down the track and chips it in the air but the ball drops well short of Morgan at deep midwicket
Watson favours the on side too and this time he gets a lot of elevation, gets down for the slog sweep and sends the ball over deep midwicket, disturbs the peace at the grass embankment
and Ponting gets to 12,000 ODI runs in style! Onions drops it short of a length and Ponting swivels, nearly loses his balance and pulls to deep square leg
gets right across his stumps and shoulders arms
gets behind the line and defends
Ponting drives on the front foot and a misfield at short cover allows a single
digs it in short and wide outside off and Watson shapes to play at it but changes and mind and watches it through to the keeper maybe expecting a wide
gets across and punches it down to mid-on
flighted on middle and leg and clipped to fine leg
bowls it flatter and quicker, he makes room and dabs it to short third man
flighted on middle and leg and pushed through the line to long-on
premeditated paddle and places it to fine leg
quick through the air and defended to cover
drops it fractionally short on the off stump and it's not the ideal length to keep Watson quiet, he seizes on it quickly and clubs it over midwicket
gets beside the line and taps it to point
runs it down to third man, these two have added 150
easy does it, drops it short again, this time Ponting swivels, manages to maintain his balance and pulls behind square, just manages to beat fine leg who's square
gets forward and taps it to the off side
gives him a hint of width outside off and he easily dabs it to third man
chops it straight to short point
not the best of pull shots but he clears the infield and manages to place it well clear of any fielder
deftly bisects the smallish gap at point and third man runs across to mop up
hangs his bat out and deftly angles it down to Strauss at short point
hits the deck hard outside off and he slashes and the top edge flies towards third man
he punishes a long hop, Watson gets on his knee and clubs it over square leg, well clear of any fielder
flighted on middle and leg, he works it to midwicket
lots of power on that, flighted on middle and leg, Watson gets his weight behind it and pushes it firmly past midwicket, really tests the fielder in the deep
gets forward and defends
chips it in the air but the ball falls in front of mid-on
stays behind the line and punches it towards mid-off
gets a bit of width outside off but chops it down to point
Wright drops the ball short on seeing the batsman advance, Ponting ends up lashing it over point
tucks a low full toss to mid-on and Shah has a shy at the stumps, Watson was in a bit of trouble there
gets beside the line and chops it down to cover
lands it on a good length on the off stump and firmly defended
he wants to finish this quickly, hits a good length on middle and Ponting picks the length early and clubs a flat six over deep square leg
gets beside the line and cuts to the off side
overpitched outside off and Watson bends his knee slightly and plays an exquisite drive to beat the arc between mid-off and cover
holds the length back outside off and he punches it wide of point
gets forward to a full delivery and drives wide of cover
full on middle and leg and pushes it to mid-on, a direct hit by Shah sends the stumps flying but the batsman's home
slightly short and he pulls to deep midwicket, puts pressure on the fielder by going for the second run
yet another pull but more behind square on the on side
bends his knee and deftly angles it towards point who dives and palms it away
fullish in length outside off and driven towards cover
wide deliveries will not help England's cause, Watson bends his knees, reaches out and cuts very firmly square of the wicket and beats point and third man comfortably
stays beside the line and chops it to the off side
walks across his stumps and chops it towards cover
gets to his hundred with a crispy cover drive, gets his bat and body behind a half volley and pierces the gap between mid-off and cover with little effort
taps it back to Bresnan
fullish outside off and driven down to sweeper cover
hits the deck hard outside off and the bouncer hurries on to Watson who swings and misses
full outside off and driven past point
stays beside the line and taps it to the off side
gets across his stumps and taps it back to the bowler

gets to his hundred with a statement of intent, Anderson drops it a fraction short and Watson swivels and clubs a flat six over deep midwicket, he raises his arms as soon as the ball flies off the bat, emotional moment for the injury-prone Watson, well done Shane
short outside off and he runs it down to third man
tucks it to the on side
goes for a booming pull and swishes at thin air

this time he connects and how! Short outside off and Watson clubs it with all his might and clears deep midwicket, the spectator at the grass embankment tries to catch it but the ball strikes his head, no wonder Watson looked so concerned for a few seconds
plays it to sweeper cove
pushes it down to backward point
not short enough to pull, he places it to square leg
opens the face of the bat and runs it down to third man
gets an inside edge but the ball trickles past the stumps
stays right behind the line and taps it to mid-on
gets behind the line again and defends
clips it towards short midwicket and tells his partner to stay back
short down the leg side and the batsman can't resist a hook, the ball balloons off the top edge and just clears Davies who leaps in vain
four less needed, friendly long hop from Collingwood and Ponting bends his knee slightly and exploits the yawning gap at deep square leg
full on the off stump and pushed to mid-off
he's making a living out of flat sixes today, friendly short delivery, he clubs it over deep square, no casualties in the crowd this time, thankfully
cuts it straight to point

if you're somewhere behind deep square leg reading this, please take cover! Watson's just having a blast bashing them around, flat and quick off the bat, this man has tremendous bat speed, luckily the kids at the grass embankment were alert enough
this time he clears wide long-on, fuller in length, he gets on his knee and enjoys a free swing of the arms
slides on the pads and the ball trickles away to square leg
gets forward to a full delivery and pushes it down to mid-off
full on middle and leg and he works it down to long-on
swivels and attempts a pull but he keeps it along the ground to fine leg
plays a checked drive down towards point and scampers a single, beats the throw at the bowler's end and Australia complete a nine-wicket rout
